**Auth Feature Implementation Checklist**
🔹 Planning & Design
- Draft design docs (flow diagrams, sequence, expected inputs/outputs).
- Define auth requirements (signup, login, JWT/session, roles, password reset, etc.).

🔹 Backend
- Create backend endpoints (/signup, /login, /logout, /refresh, /me, etc.).
- Test backend endpoints with Postman (happy & edge cases).
- Add validation & error handling (Yup/Joi/express-validator).

🔹 Frontend Integration (MVP)
- Build just enough FE components (forms, API hooks, context/provider).
- Connect FE → BE endpoints.
- Test FE manually (signup/login/logout flow works).

🔹 Automated Testing
- Write backend tests (unit + integration, e.g., Jest + Supertest).
- Write frontend tests (form validation, API responses, protected routes).
- Run BE + FE tests together.

🔹 Security
Add auth security checks:
- Secure password hashing (bcrypt/argon2).
- Token expiry + refresh flow.
- Rate limiting / brute-force protection.
- CORS, CSRF, HTTPS enforcement.
- Retest BE + FE (ensure security didn’t break functionality).

🔹 UI & Cleanup
- Add basic styling for FE (just enough for usability).
- Refactor & clean up codebase (remove unused code, add comments).

🔹 Final Validation
- Run full test cycle (manual + automated).
- Confirm edge cases (expired token, invalid creds, multiple sessions).
- Mark the feature as ready for release.
